a:2:{s:7:"content";s:1271:"<p>To post to this knowledge use the workflow defined below:</p>
<ul>
<li>open template in Atom with 'ctrl-alt-n'</li>
<li>set visible to <code>true</code> in the yaml frontmatter block</li>
<li>set the title to whatever you want to appear in the menu nav</li>
<li>set the category to <code>KB</code></li>
<li>use a relevant tag such as those below or add a new one:
<ul>
<li>linux</li>
<li>bash</li>
<li>kvm</li>
<li>aws</li>
<li>docker</li>
</ul></li>
<li>start writing and when done save to a new folder under the knowledge-base folder with naming convention in lowercase and separated by dashes (example: linux-admin)</li>
<li>name the file <code>default.md</code></li>
</ul>
<p>To clarify, all posts in this knowledge base are files in their own folder. The folder is created first then the file is always named <code>default.md</code></p>
